text: Lerissa Henry (born August 18, 1997) is a sprinter from the Federated States of Micronesia. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 100 metres race; her time of 13.53 seconds in the preliminary round did not qualify her for the first round. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Federated States of Micronesia female sprinters Category:Olympic track and field athletes of the Federated States of Micronesia Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
